name: Cozy cabin style apartment - lower level
description:
Wood paneled cozy studio apartment nestled beneath mature oak trees. It was built in the late 80s with features that resemble both a woodsy cabin and a ship's cabin.

Separate from the main residence, on the lower level of the residence, with its own private entrance. Quiet, peaceful neighborhood, walking distance to Topanga State Park; minutes to Topanga Beach, Malibu, Pacific Coast Highway, or Woodland Hills, restaurants, local shops, stores, parks, hiking, community activities.
neighborhood_overview:
Topanga is surrounded by Topanga State Park, the largest wilderness area located within a city limit in the United States.

Topanga is home to a large population of native species of plants, trees, birds, and animals and insects - red tail hawks, coyotes, mountain lions, bobcats, owls, raccoons, foxes, lizards, snakes, venemous and non-venemous, native live oaks. We live in the midst of an unspoiled natural environment. Topanga was recently certified as a Wildlife Habitat by The National Wildlife Federation, additionally, our home is certified as a Wildlife Habitat.

Hiking is a major outdoor activity. There are also some areas for recreational biking - you will have to sort that out yourself. There is always music at several restaurants and small venues in town. There are a number of yoga and pilates studios in the area, and the beautiful coastline is 20 minutes away.

The Topanga community is know as a haven for artists, musicians, actors, filmakers, a
host_about:
I am an artist/designer, color consultant, and father. 
My wife and I purchased this property in beautiful Topanga in 2015. We are both artists, our studios are on the premises, It is a blessing to live and work here in the canyon. I enjoy restoring and collecting antiques and modernist collectibles, hiking, gardening, astronomy, and music. It's an amazing place to raise a kid and create.

description:
Welcome to Huntington Park, affectionately known as HP> You'll be staying in a 1B/1B casita that we have been calling home for the past 2 years. There is a small backyard where you can smoke, chill and/or relax. 4/20 friendly, just please keep all smoking outside.

neighborhood_overview:
You will be in a castia that is 1 of 3 units on the property. Our landlord lives in the front house and we have a neighbor across the courtyard. A little long hair pup name Pumpkin will occasionally be in the courtyard. She is a friendly and sweet pup so don't be afraid to say hello!

Huntington Park is a working class neighborhood rooted in the Latino culture LA has become famous for. We are near Salt Late Park which is great for tennis, basketball and a morning jog!



We are a 5 minute drive from the historic Pacific Blvd and 20 minutes from Downtown Los Angeles.

neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to Koreatown, one of Los Angeles' most vibrant and culturally rich neighborhoods! Located just a few miles from downtown, Koreatown, often referred to as K-town, offers a unique blend of historic charm and modern amenities, making it a must-visit destination for both tourists and locals.

Culture and Cuisine
Koreatown is renowned for its bustling nightlife, eclectic dining options, and cultural landmarks. You'll find an array of authentic Korean BBQ restaurants, trendy cafes, and dessert spots serving everything from traditional pastries to innovative boba tea creations. The area is also home to several late-night eateries and 24-hour establishments, reflecting its lively, around-the-clock energy.

Entertainment and Nightlife
K-town boasts a thriving entertainment scene with numerous karaoke bars, stylish lounges, and nightclubs. Whether you're in the mood for singing your heart out or dancing the night away, there's always something happening in K
